OL,3,C'I collapsed on mile 24':The dangers
OL,4,Cof taking ibuprofen before a marathon
OL,6,FThe ibuprofen Max took had triggered a
OL,7,Fheat stroke, causing rhabdomialaysis -
OL,8,Fa serious medical condition where the
OL,9,Fbreakdown of muscle tissue leads to
OL,10,Fthe release of muscle contents into
OL,11,Fthe bloodstream.
OL,13,FThis release can cause various
OL,14,Fcomplications, including kidney damage
OL,15,Fand potentially life-threatening
OL,16,Fconditions like acute kidney failure.
OL,18,FMax was moved to the kidney unit for a
OL,19,Ffurther two weeks. After three weeks
OL,20,Fin hospital, Max was released, but the
OL,21,Feffects of his heat stroke persisted.
