OL,3,C'I collapsed on mile 24':The dangers
OL,4,Cof taking ibuprofen before a marathon
OL,6,FThis extra stress on the kidneys can
OL,7,Fhave a range of consequences, not all
OL,8,Fas extreme as Max's experience.
OL,10,F"You might just feel a bit rubbish and
OL,11,Frun a bit slower or maybe become
OL,12,Freally sick, and maybe ending up
OL,13,Fneeding to go to hospital," he said.
OL,15,FAs TCS London Marathon celebrate its
OL,16,F45th anniversary on Sunday, Dr
OL,17,FFitzpatrick urges runners to be wary
OL,18,Fof taking painkillers.
